description:
Define the `BackingFs` trait in `ize-lib/src/backing_fs/mod.rs`. This trait abstracts directory-relative filesystem operations so the FUSE passthrough layer doesn't depend on a specific backing implementation.

## Trait surface

```rust
pub trait BackingFs: Send + Sync {
    // Stat
    fn stat(&self, rel: &Path) -> io::Result<libc::stat>;
    fn fstat(&self, fd: RawFd) -> io::Result<libc::stat>;

    // File I/O
    fn open_file(&self, rel: &Path, flags: i32, mode: u32) -> io::Result<RawFd>;
    fn pread(&self, fd: RawFd, buf: &mut [u8], offset: i64) -> io::Result<usize>;
    fn pwrite(&self, fd: RawFd, data: &[u8], offset: i64) -> io::Result<usize>;
    fn fsync(&self, fd: RawFd) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn close_fd(&self, fd: RawFd);
    fn ftruncate(&self, fd: RawFd, size: u64) -> io::Result<()>;

    // Directory ops
    fn mkdir(&self, rel: &Path, mode: u32) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn rmdir(&self, rel: &Path) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn readdir(&self, rel: &Path) -> io::Result<Vec<DirEntry>>;

    // Path ops
    fn unlink(&self, rel: &Path) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn rename(&self, old: &Path, new: &Path) -> io::Result<()>;

    // Metadata
    fn chmod(&self, rel: &Path, mode: u32) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn chown(&self, rel: &Path, uid: Option<u32>, gid: Option<u32>) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn utimens(&self, rel: &Path, atime: &libc::timespec, mtime: &libc::timespec) -> io::Result<()>;
    fn access(&self, rel: &Path, mask: i32) -> io::Result<()>;

    // Filesystem
    fn statvfs(&self) -> io::Result<libc::statvfs>;
}
```

## Also define

- `DirEntry` struct: `{ ino: u64, dtype: u8, name: OsString }`
- `pub mod libc_impl;` declaration
- Re-exports in `mod.rs`

## Design notes

- All paths are relative to the backing store root (empty path = root)
- `RawFd` used for file handles — caller is responsible for close_fd
- `io::Result` throughout — raw errno propagation
- `Send + Sync` required since FUSE calls from multiple threads

Add module declarations and re-exports so the new code is accessible.

## Changes

### `ize-lib/src/lib.rs`
```rust
pub mod backing_fs;
```

### `ize-lib/src/filesystems/mod.rs`
```rust
pub mod passthrough_fd;
pub use passthrough_fd::FdPassthroughFS;
```

### `ize-lib/src/backing_fs/mod.rs`
```rust
pub mod libc_impl;
pub use libc_impl::LibcBackingFs;
// trait re-export already in mod.rs
```

### `ize-lib/Cargo.toml`
Verify existing deps are sufficient. The backing_fs/libc.rs only needs `libc` (already a dependency). No new crate deps expected.

Rewrite the `fuse-fd-poc` binary to use the library types instead of inline implementations. This validates the library architecture end-to-end.

## Changes to fuse-fd-poc/Cargo.toml
```toml
[dependencies]
ize-lib = { path = "../ize-lib" }
fuser = "0.15.1"
libc = "0.2"
log = "0.4"
env_logger = "0.10"
# remove nix — no longer needed directly
```

## Changes to fuse-fd-poc/src/main.rs

Replace inline `FdPassthroughFS` + `sys_*` functions with:

```rust
use ize_lib::backing_fs::{BackingFs, LibcBackingFs};
use ize_lib::filesystems::FdPassthroughFS;

// 1. Open base_fd (still done here, before mount)
let base_fd = unsafe { libc::open(..., O_RDONLY | O_DIRECTORY) };

// 2. Create backing store
let backing = LibcBackingFs::new(base_fd);

// 3. Create FUSE filesystem
let fs = FdPassthroughFS::new(Box::new(backing), mount_point.clone());

// 4. Mount
let guard = fuser::spawn_mount2(fs, &mount_point, &options)?;
```

Keep the same 7-step validation logic. The test should produce identical results to the current inline PoC.

## Success criteria

- `cargo run -p fuse-fd-poc` passes all 7 validation steps
- No inline sys_* wrappers remain in the binary
- Binary is <100 lines (just setup + validation)
